# Version Update Rule

When updating package versions in this monorepo, ensure ALL references are updated consistently across the entire codebase.

## Files to Update When Changing Package Versions:

### Package Files:
- [packages/nest_core/pubspec.yaml](mdc:packages/nest_core/pubspec.yaml) - Core package version
- [packages/nest_flutter/pubspec.yaml](mdc:packages/nest_flutter/pubspec.yaml) - Flutter package version  
- [packages/nest_frog/pubspec.yaml](mdc:packages/nest_frog/pubspec.yaml) - Frog package version

### Package Documentation:
- [packages/nest_core/README.md](mdc:packages/nest_core/README.md) - Version references in installation
- [packages/nest_core/CHANGELOG.md](mdc:packages/nest_core/CHANGELOG.md) - New version entry
- [packages/nest_flutter/README.md](mdc:packages/nest_flutter/README.md) - Version references in installation
- [packages/nest_flutter/CHANGELOG.md](mdc:packages/nest_flutter/CHANGELOG.md) - New version entry
- [packages/nest_frog/README.md](mdc:packages/nest_frog/README.md) - Version references in installation
- [packages/nest_frog/CHANGELOG.md](mdc:packages/nest_frog/CHANGELOG.md) - New version entry

### Documentation Site:
- [docs/pages/getting-started.mdx](mdc:docs/pages/getting-started.mdx) - Installation examples for all platforms
- [docs/pages/core-guide.mdx](mdc:docs/pages/core-guide.mdx) - nest_core version references
- [docs/pages/flutter-guide.mdx](mdc:docs/pages/flutter-guide.mdx) - nest_flutter version references
- [docs/pages/frog-guide.mdx](mdc:docs/pages/frog-guide.mdx) - nest_frog version references

## Version Update Checklist:

1. **Update pubspec.yaml files** with new version numbers
2. **Add CHANGELOG.md entries** with release date and features
3. **Update README.md files** with new version in installation examples
4. **Update documentation guides** with new version references
5. **Check all code examples** use correct import statements
6. **Verify dependency references** match the new versions

## Version Format:
- Use semantic versioning (e.g., `0.1.0`, `0.1.1`, `1.0.0`)
- Use caret notation in examples (e.g., `^0.1.1`)
- Keep consistent date format in changelogs: `YYYY-MM-DD`

